<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>lash out at something • lash out on something</xh5><p> <i>lash out at something—</i>make a sudden and violent verbal attack on smth.: The speaker <u>lashed out at</u> the government’s new tax laws.</p><p> <i>lash out on something</i>—(coll.) spend freely on smth.; pay a lot of money for smth.: Can we afford to <u>lash out on</u> a new car?</p> </entry>
